messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false
- POST acceptable: true
- OPTIONS acceptable: false
- TRACE acceptable: false
- GET acceptable: false
- PUT acceptable: true
- DELETE acceptable: false
- PATCH acceptable: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the endpoint path is exactly the method-level value.
- addNewRingsItem is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings", method = RequestMethod.POST) — therefore POST is explicitly supported for that path.
- editRingsItem uses the same path with method = RequestMethod.PUT — therefore PUT is explicitly supported for that path.
- No handler methods for GET, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE, HEAD, or OPTIONS are present in the code for this path. Following the instruction to base acceptance on the code (not on framework runtime behavior), those methods are not acceptable.
